(2, 2, 'Diploma of Building and Construction', 'diploma-of-building-and-construction', 1, 'In most places of the world, a verified Undergraduate degree values more than Diploma courses. But does it provide practical knowledge? Unfortunately, not!', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In most places of the world, a verified Undergraduate degree values more than Diploma courses. But does it provide practical knowledge? Unfortunately, not! Diploma courses, in this context, fill the gap. Within a short time, one can achieve knowledge-based practical certifications which can help in building their career. Moreover, from the Australian perspective, the practical-based diploma courses are regarded as much more efficient as proof of their hands-on skills. There are plenty of diploma courses to choose from but in this article, the spotlight is on the Diploma of Building and Construction.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The diploma course in Building and Construction helps an individual to master the professional skills and knowledge required for the management, supervision, and administration of residential, industrial, and commercial building projects. If anyone is willing to start up their own building business then Diploma courses are the right choice.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In the context of Australia, this type of qualification has been structured to satisfy the requirements of the building professional who coordinates the development of a building, taking responsibility for the general completion of the task, including selecting contractors, overseeing the work and its quality, and cooperating with the client. The building professional also can be the appropriately licensed person with responsibility under the relevant building licensing authority within the state or territory.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Out of numberless institutions providing Diploma courses on Constructions and Building, Alpha Training &amp; Recognition Pty Ltd (ATR) is known as one of the best nationally recognised training providers all around Australia, prominent for helping the students to assess their skills. It offers accredited courses and Recognition of Prior Learning (RPL) service for Australians and the nationwide building industry. It also provides quality training and face to face delivery as part of its services.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In addition to being nationally recognized training and builder&rsquo;s recognition consultants for nationwide applicants, ATR provides a clear assessment of whether the student is eligible to start their qualification through the Recognition of Prior Learning (RPL) assessment program. If the student happens not to be eligible for Recognition of Prior Learning (RPL), it offers full face to face accredited courses that will help the students to obtain their qualifications and achieve your goals</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The institution is run by building industry experts having over 15 years of experience in the construction industry. It offers a solution that ensures that the students get the qualification that they want without having to sit through long and drawn out training courses.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This course teaches an individual the principles, techniques, and regulations of the building industry for all types of medium-rise and wide-span buildings. By learning from industry professionals, cones can develop specialist skills and knowledge to run a small-to-medium construction business.&nbsp; The designed modules focus on some key roles like quantity surveying, planning and scheduling of labor and materials, selecting contractors, managing project risk and quality, supervising worksites, construction technology, managing workplace safety, and small business finance. The course will help an individual to enhance their skills in the industry as well as giving the opportunity to progress their career. ATR also offers advice with Builder&rsquo;s Registration to make things easier for those working in the construction industry.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Construction isn\'t always building sites, but about building a much bigger picture: the design, coordination, and control of a project from inception to delivery. The Building and Construction courses at ATR are primarily designed for trade professionals to gain skills recognition and training that is recognised across Australia.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For better learning outcomes, the institution is equipped with modern high-tech labs and dynamic workshops including a concrete laboratory, survey laboratory, engine laboratory, soldering/construction laboratories, power systems laboratory, and computer workstations with simulation and modeling software. These facilities are provided with an intention to ease the student&rsquo;s learning path and eventually help them to reach their ultimate goals.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Whatever the students learn at ATR has direct links to the real world. Students have the opportunity to practically develop their skills by utilizing their theoretical knowledge. It aims at crafting the students in such a manner that they become job-ready as soon as they graduate.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Students learn from teachers having valuable industry contacts and the latest industry-standard skills.&nbsp; They also develop links with industry and professional experience through site visits, industry projects, live work, industry-endorsed workshops, and industry simulation.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As a dedicated student, they must invest 15-18 hours a week for self-study and learning and assessment activities to accelerate their overall academic growth. They must also complete: - Prepare to work safely in the construction industry unit before a workplace visit.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The maximum duration of the course duration is 12 months and does not take into account any existing knowledge and skills. The course may be shorter depending on the students\' prior academic background and/or relevant work experience where applicable.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Students will get training in various fields such as:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Apply principles of OHS risk management</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Manage project quality</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Manage project risk</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Register building codes for the development process for low rise building projects</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Select and prepare a construction contract</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Determine and produce estimated costs for building and construction projects</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Register structural concepts to residential low rise constructions</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Produce labour and material schedules for ordering</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Prepare and evaluate tender documentation</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Prepare simple building sketches and drawings</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Register building codes to the event process for medium rise building projects</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Keep track of the costing systems on medium rise building and construction projects</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Supervise the design of on-site medium rise building or construction work</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&nbsp;Supervise and apply quality standards to the choice of building and construction materials</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Select and manage building and construction contractors</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Regulate the legal obligations of a building or construction contractor</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Determine services format and link procedures to medium rise construction projects</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Manage construction work</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Apply structural principles to the development of medium-rise buildings</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">On completion of the course, students will gain the skills to work as a Site Manager, Licensed or Registered Builder, Construction Manager, or Project Manager with this Diploma of Building and Construction.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Therefore, if an individual is willing to develop a career in Building and Construction, then this course is the right fit to invest in.</span></p>', NULL, NULL, 'In most places of the world, a verified Undergraduate degree values more than Diploma courses. But does it provide practical knowledge? Unfortunately, not!', '311220-101220.jpg', NULL, '2020-12-31 17:57:20', '2021-07-17 15:19:52'),
(3, 2, 'Top 2 Skills Needed To Compete For Construction Jobs', 'top-2-skills-needed-to-compete-for-construction-jobs', 1, 'The demand for skilled workers to fill construction jobs is increasing day by day.', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The demand for skilled workers to fill construction jobs is increasing day by day. If an individual is in high school or has just graduated or might be returning from active duty or are looking to make a career change, developing some of the basic technical skills is necessary</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If anyone is interested in joining the construction industry there are basic skills that they need to learn. These basic skills are critical in order to compete for construction jobs.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Curious about the skills needed? There are skills that are different from specific trades and construction jobs.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The 2 Foundation Skills to help compete for Construction Jobs are:</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Reading a Tape Measure</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Know the Tools of the Trade</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Top 2 Skills Needed To Compete For Construction Jobs</span></h2>\r\n<h3><strong>Reading a Tape Measure</strong></h3>\r\n<p><strong><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../blogImages/1614488127.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"674\" height=\"447\" /></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It is an important skill for an individual to know to read and use a tape measure. It is essential to be able to use a tape measure in any construction or trade-related jobs. It is also an important life skill. Without it, one will not be able to do simple tasks that are required to maintain a home.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Construction projects require precise measurements. Cutting grades for excavating requires measuring. Measurements are necessary for stringing electrical wire and mounting boxes.&nbsp; While setting up a roof installation, accurate measurements are needed. More or less, all construction-related jobs need the skill of reading a tape measure.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Learning how to read a tape measure is an important life skill that one needs to master. This skill can be used for both personal and professional works. Failing to know this important skill can limit the ability to grow and take on more responsibility in their job. It will be a major limiting factor in their earning potential if someone does not have this important skill.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Know the Tools of the Trade</strong></h3>\r\n<p><strong><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../blogImages/1614488479.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"674\" height=\"447\" /></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Various construction jobs need various tools of the trade to complete the work smoothly. It is necessary to master the tools of the trade for faster growth in the construction industry.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One must know the tools of the trade for any construction jobs. Those who want to be pro in this field are suggested to ask a lot of questions and listen to the answers carefully. An individual needs to talk with their supervisor or foreman while they are traveling to the job site.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Successfully learning the tools of the trade requires an individual to practice their listening skills. For most people, listening is a weakness. One must ask their questions focusing on the answer that is being given. And if they do not understand an answer, they should ask a follow-up question. It is also necessary to know the name of the tool and if it has any short names. It is also suggested to learn when and where the tools are used.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Some extra knowledge can be gained by watching online tutorials about specific tools. Search the tools on the internet. Also, one can go to stores and walk through the tool section. Hardware stores are great resources for new employees in the construction industry to learn more about the tools of their trade.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In terms of the construction world, out of countless institutions providing Diploma courses on Constructions and Building, Alpha Training &amp; Recognition Pty Ltd (ATR) is known as one of the finest nationally recognised training providers all around Australia, prominent for helping the students to assess their skills. It offers highly recognised courses and Recognition of Prior Learning (RPL) service for Australians and in the building industry, ubiquitously. It also caters to quality training and face-to-face delivery as part of its services.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With the training from Alpha Training Recognition, an individual will surely land a job in the construction world.</span></p>', NULL, NULL, 'The demand for skilled workers to fill construction jobs is increasing day by day.', '280221-050204.jpg', NULL, '2021-02-28 12:08:04', '2021-07-17 15:20:11'),
